.B
\fBcommon_option_tls13() ::\fR
\fB          {supported_groups, [group()]} |\fR
\fB          {key_update_at, KeyUpdateAt :: pos_integer()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Common options to both client and server for TLS-1.3.

{supported_groups, Groups}
.RS 2
Key exchange option

.PP
TLS 1.3 introduces the "supported_groups" extension, which is used for negotiating the key-exchange parameters in a TLS 1.3 handshake. Both client and server can specify a list of parameters that they are willing to use.

.PP
If not specified it will use a default list that can be obtained by calling \fIssl:groups(default).\fR that is filtered based on the installed crypto library version.


.RE

{key_update_at, KeyUpdateAt}
.RS 2
Session key renewal

.PP
Configures the maximum amount of bytes that can be sent on a TLS 1.3 connection before an automatic key update is performed.

.PP
There are cryptographic limits on the amount of plaintext which can be safely encrypted under a given set of keys. The current default ensures that data integrity will not be breached with probability greater than \fI1/2^57\fR. For more information see Limits on Authenticated Encryption Use in TLS.


.RE


