\fBcrl_cache_opts() ::\fR
\fB          {Module :: atom(),\fR
\fB           {DbHandle :: internal | term(), Args :: list()}}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Options for using built-in CRL cache support.

.PP
Specify how to perform lookup and caching of certificate revocation lists (CRLs). \fIModule\fR defaults to \fIssl_crl_cache\fR with \fIDbHandle\fR being \fIinternal\fR, and \fIArgs\fR being \fI[]\fR.

.PP
There are two implementations available:

ssl_crl_cache
.RS 2
Implementation 1

.PP
This module maintains a cache of CRLs. CRLs can be added to the cache using \fIssl_crl_cache:insert/1\fR, and can optionally be automatically fetched through HTTP if the following argument is specified:


.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fB\fI{http, timeout()}\fR\fR

.PP
Enables fetching of CRLs specified as http URIs in X.509 certificate extensions. Requires the Inets application.

.RE

ssl_crl_hash_dir
.RS 2
Implementation 2

.PP
This module makes use of a directory where CRLs are stored in files named by the hash of the issuer name.

.PP
The file names consist of eight hexadecimal digits followed by \fI.rN\fR, where \fIN\fR is an integer, for example \fI1a2b3c4d.r0\fR. For the first version of the CRL, \fIN\fR starts at zero, and for each new version, \fIN\fR is incremented by one. The OpenSSL utility \fIc_rehash\fR creates symlinks according to this pattern.

.PP
For a given hash value, this module finds all consecutive \fI.r*\fR files starting from zero, and those files taken together make up the revocation list. CRL files with \fInextUpdate\fR fields in the past or issued by a different CA that happens to have the same name hash are excluded.

.PP
The following argument is required:


.sp
