{verify, Verify}
.RS 2
Verify certificates.

.PP
Client certificates are an optional part of the TLS protocol. A server performs X.509 certificate path validation only in \fIverify_peer\fR mode. By default the server is in \fIverify_none\fR mode and, hence, will not send an certificate request to the client. When using \fIverify_peer\fR you may also want to specify the options \fIfail_if_no_peer_cert\fR and \fIcertificate_authorities\fR.


