.PP
In pre-shared key session ticket resumption, there is no certificate exchange involved. Therefore, \fIssl:peercert/1\fR will not return the peer certificate, as it is only communicated during the initial handshake. To associate the client certificate from the original handshake with the tickets it issues, the server options \fIstateful_with_cert\fR or \fIstateless_with_cert\fR can be used.

