.PP
If no filter function is supplied for some part, the default behavior treats it as a filter function that returns \fItrue\fR. For examples, see Customizing cipher suites . Additionally, this function also filters the cipher suites to exclude cipher suites not supported by the crypto library used by the OTP Crypto application, meaning that \fIssl:filter_cipher_suites(Suites, [])\fR is equivalent to applying only the filters for crypto library support.


.RE
.B
\fBformat_error(Error) -> ReasonStr\fR
\fB                      when\fR
\fB                          Error :: {error, reason()} | reason(),\fR
